  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Slice your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into discs and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602247307526-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602247307526-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602247307526-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602247307526-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1602247307526-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, cut your <strong>paneer</strong> into small, bite-sized cubes</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> paneer</strong> <strong>cubes</strong> and cook for 3-5 min until golden, turning occasionally for even colouring</p><p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>golden paneer</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602247325316-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602247325316-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602247325316-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602247325316-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1602247325316-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the paneer is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Dice your <strong>tomato[es]</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602247337209-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602247337209-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602247337209-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602247337209-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1602247337209-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to the heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and <strong>black mustard seeds</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> and <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602247348688-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602247348688-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602247348688-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602247348688-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1602247348688-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the<strong> diced tomato</strong>, <strong>garam masala </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for an initial 2-3 min or until the tomato has softened</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[275ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once the tomato has softened, add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 30 secs</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1602247357055-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1602247357055-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1602247357055-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1602247357055-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1602247357055-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong>,<strong> golden paneer</strong>,<strong> mango chutney</strong> and <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>paneer & pea curry</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly, then transfer the <strong>paneer & pea curry</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1602247387454-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1602247387454-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1602247387454-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1602247387454-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1602247387454-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Arrange the<strong> softened potato discs</strong> on top (careful – they will be hot!)<strong> </strong>and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining chilli flakes </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), then put the dish in the oven for 15-20 min or until bubbling and golden – this is your <strong>potato-topped paneer & pea curry pie</strong></p><p>Once the pie has been cooking for 10 min, reboil a kettle</p><p>Trim the <strong>green beans</strong>, then add them to a pot and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1602247417944-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1602247417944-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1602247417944-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1602247417944-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1602247417944-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>potato-topped paneer & pea curry pie</strong> in the centre of the table and serve with the <strong>green beans </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
